description.narrative:
The project title “Assistance to the newly arrived Central African Refugees in Garoua Boulai and Gada subdivision in the East Region of Cameroon” will be implemented in Garoua Boulai and Gado in East region from 05 February to 22 March 2021 within 45 days. 

The project aims to improved living condition of 6775 central African Refugees and host community (5 655 refugees and 1120 host community peoples) through the&#58;
-  Distribution of NFI kits (household items or cocking items, clothing, blankets, mosquito nets.) to 1999 households;
- Set up of hand washing facilities in public spaces;
- Hygiene promotion/ awareness raising campaigns on Wash and COVID 19 prevention (Door to Door);
- Distribution of wash kits (buckets, jerry cans, cups, soaps, 20 liter canisters) to 1999 households;
- PDM activities and
- Set up a feedback Mechanism

The project will be carried out in collaboration with beneficiaries and all partners. In order to make sure that activities are well implemented, Plan will continuous to attend in weekly Coordination meetings where their realisation and challenges will be shared. Government partners will be frequently informed of Plan's Intervention even the challenge in order to facilitate the interventions. A feedback mechanism will be set up in order to make sure that beneficiaries are fully engaged, their need is addressed and Do No Harm Principle is respected.

Gender&#58; This humanitarians’ intervention has targeted different groups of vulnerable people including Women, men, boys and girls.  In terms of gender and coordination, the goal is to ensure that a quality and effective response is done considering the specific groups (households lead by women and young boys or girls, men and boys). Advocacy will be made in coordination meeting and coordination platforms in order to respond to the needs per gender (women, girls, boys and men). Actions will be taken to ensure participation of different groups, women, men, girls and boys in the coordination meetings with leader's committees, government actors and NGOs in the field.
